    "However, the order in which the examples were presented does have a major impact on the per-class performance.",
    "Table 6 shows how the class presented first biases the results.",
    "None of these phenomenon have been observed in the fine-tuned version of the model in this dataset Operational ResultsLatency on an encoder-only model is between one to two orders of magnitude lower than on decoder-only models.",
    "The main reason for the large discrepancy is the way responses are produced: while encoder-only models only need a pass to produce a probability vector, decoderonly models produce one token at a time until the end-of-sentence token is produced or they reach the limit of allowed tokens.",
